2)WRITING A FILE
      ->when you use writing mode  the previous data of inside the files are removed or override
      ->only the new writing mode  to creates data's are placed in inside of file.Old data's are removes or override in file
#program
file=open("name.txt","w")
file.write("vijay\n")
file.write("nithya\n")
file.write("jacob\n")
file.write("saroja\n")
file.write("chinna thambi"
file.close()                   #now these 5 names are filled in file(name.txt).the old 'aravinth' and 'titus' names are overrided

file=open("name.txt","r")      #in file handling, we can print the file using read mode only
print(file.read())

#output
vijay
nithya
jacob
saroja
chinna thambi

3)APPENDING TO A FILE
        ->when you use 'a' the append mode this add new data's to the old data's 
    
#program
file=open("name.txt","a")
file.write("Jesus")     #in inside of name file we previosly have 5 data's, now one more data is included to the file 
file.close()

file=open("name.txt","r")
